node: Build via "python3 build_mininn.py" in .venv (CMake + Ninja, clang/clang++). Build erfolgreich; gtest-main, demo und Python-Modul mininn_capi wurden erzeugt.

2025-12-22 (Europe/Berlin): Linux build + tooling setup.
Upstream project is VS-focused; added/used custom Linux CMake build (CMakeLists.txt not from upstream). Also excluded CUDA sources to avoid cudart linkage.
Built: cmake -S . -B build && cmake --build build -j  => build/libCAS2D.so

Created harness: cas_harness.c (calls CAS_initialize -> CAS_supplyImage(256x256 RGBA) -> CAS_sharpenImage(mode=0, 0.5, 0.5) -> CAS_destroy once). Native run OK.

Tooling:
- oclgrind 21.10 --check-api initially failed at clCreateImage with CL_INVALID_VALUE (image_format) when using cl::ImageFormat(CL_sRGBA, CL_UNORM_INT8) in CASImpl.cpp.
- Applied tool-compat patch: CL_sRGBA -> CL_RGBA in CAS-2D-Lib/CASImpl.cpp; after patch oclgrind --check-api ./cas_harness runs through (no API errors reported).

Interpretation: likely Oclgrind limitation / portability issue around sRGB image formats; project has no runtime fallback/check for supported image formats.
Artifacts recommended: save patch as patches/cas2d-oclgrind-rgba.patch; keep harness and oclgrind logs.

CMake build (WITH_OPENCL=ON, WITH_SDL=ON); test_clNBody2D only runs with CWD=build_cpp/sketches_OCL/Nbody.

notes_detail      = Minimal fix: <algorithm> include in Selection.h + __local shared array in cl/nbody.cl moved to kernel top level. Oclgrind --check-api runs without further API errors.

Build via official build.sh stops in vendored assimp (SceneCombiner.cpp, memcpy on non-trivially copyable aiFace/aiMeshMorphKey treated as -Werror by clang 20); fixing requires patching dependency, out-of-scope for study.

Linux build ok (CMake, OpenCL 3.0 ICD). Oclgrind --check-api auf CLIc-Tests zeigt systematischen clGetDeviceInfo-Misuse: CL_DEVICE_MAX_WORK_GROUP_SIZE wird an zwei Stellen mit sizeof(cl_uint) statt sizeof(size_t) abgefragt; Rückgabecodes werden ignoriert ? CL_INVALID_VALUE und Heap-Korruption unter Oclgrind, native Tests bleiben grün.
Ran oclgrind --check-api on Extrae OpenCL example (vadd) after switching DEVICE to DEFAULT; no OpenCL runtime errors detected.
